reviews.review_text: Crispy The most crisp recording i have heard to date by far best matrix ever just check out the eyes
No way No way this is a soundboard. Either that or the mix is way off.

in regards to this not being a sbd This is a matrix not a straight soundboard. Personally I like it and put a lot of time and effort into this. Not sure why you say that it is not a soundboard, clearly you can here that it is a sbd/aud mix. I would like to know what others think, maybe some suggestions on improvements for the future.

Sound quality Did I miss something? This matrix sounded pretty good to me. The only echo I noticed was straight from the audience source, I believe. I will listen again, but I doubt I'll be revising my review. I appreciate getting a SB and AUD mix. The CMiller copy is certainly more clear (always is), but the audience's excitement is toned way down. I will sacrifice a little clarity. 

As for the advice requested for making a better matrix--I suggest instead of the usual 60-40 mix, try a 70-30 mix; although, I have never seen/heard a 70-30.
